According to CEO John Bruce, the idea behind Inrupt is that the company uses resources, processes and appropriate skills to make Solid available to everyone.
The company currently includes Berners-Lee, Bruce, some developers hired to work on this project, as well as a community of volunteer programmers, and a security platform acquired by IBM.
Starting this week, technology developers around the world will be able to create their own decentralized apps with the tools available on the Inrupt website.
Berners-Lee said that he and his team will not exchange views with Facebook and Google about whether a comprehensive change is to be made in which their entire business models will be completely redesigned overnight.
“We do not ask for your permission.”
